  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators predict that decreased heart rate variability and poor sleep quality will&#xD;
      be significantly correlated with higher self-reported anxiety following brain injury.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Acute rehabilitation inpatients with moderate-to-severe brain injury will wear biosensors&#xD;
      that track total sleep time and heart-rate variability for up to 1 week. During this time the&#xD;
      participants will also complete surveys regarding symptoms of anxiety. The investigators&#xD;
      hypothesize that decreased heart rate variability and poor sleep quality will be&#xD;
      significantly correlated with higher self-reported anxiety following brain injury.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
